He said something along the lines of "when we came out and were knew EXACTLY what we wanted. We had a vision." And from 99% of other bands I would think that was narcissistic as fuck, but coming from everyone in the room knew he was totally right. It gave me a while new perspective on them. Chester had his struggles (I mean everyone struggles) but I think the band helped him so much. I hope all of you are able to find peace and love in your life. None of us deserve to go out like Chester Bennington, Chris Cornell, and my dad. RIP gentlemen.
